<br>
After weighing the alternatives, NERVA was steered to be developed as an upper stage for a Saturn V (and the never-built) NOVA.<br>
No actual rocket was ever built. Only various test engines.<br>
Both the Saturn V and the NERVA died in 1973.<br>
(I saw the last Saturn V (Skylab) launch from the press site at KSC. It was incredible)<br>
